cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper presents a method for learning nonlinear transformations of multiple views of data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper specifically focuses on the use of deep learning techniques for this task, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also applies the method to two distinct datasets for different downstream tasks, including phonetic transcription and recommending hashtags on Twitter, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CV (Computer Vision), depending on the specific focus of the application. Overall, cs.LG is the most likely category, followed by cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
